Data were corrected for dead time.
Each module with dimensions of 18.3cm x 35.6cm x
12.7cm was read out using two Photonis XP4572B 12.7
cm diameter photomultiplier tubes. The two modules
stacked on top of each other give the detector system
dimensions of 36.6 cm high x 35.6 cm wide normal to
the neutron beam. Although the scintillator is
capable of pulse shape discrimination, this property
was not used in present experiment. Detector was placed
at effective flight path of (99.95+-0.07) m.
Neutron flux was monitored using two
RS-P6-2403-121 and Amperex B300D fission chambers,
which were located 9 m from the neutron target.
